17 (C) Can be mathematically identified; and
18 (D) Is equivalent to the possession of a physical license.
19 (2) 'License' shall have the same meaning as provided in Code Section 43-1-34.
20 (3) 'Other board' shall have the same meaning as provided in Code Section 43-1-34.
21 (4) 'Service member' shall have the same meaning as provided in Code Section 43-1-34.
22 (5) 'State' shall have the same meaning as provided in Code Section 43-1-35.
23 (6) 'Transitioning service member' shall have the same meaning as provided in Code
24 Section 43-1-34.
25 (b) No later than July 1, 2026, each professional licensing board and other board shall
26 adopt rules and regulations implementing a process by which spouses of service members,
27 spouses of transitioning service members, and transitioning service members may qualify
28 for digitally verifiable licenses for each profession, business, or trade for which licenses
29 are issued. Such digitally verifiable licenses shall be issued for all types of licenses issued
30 by such professional licensing board or other board, including, but not limited to,
31 temporary licenses, licenses by endorsement, expedited licenses, or a combination thereof.
32 Such rules and regulations shall include a process by which a physical license shall be
33 issued upon request in addition to or in the place of a digitally verifiable license.
34 (c) Any professional licensing board or other board created after June 30, 2026, shall adopt
35 within one year of its creation the rules and regulations required by subsection (b) of this
36 Code section."
37 SECTION 2.
38 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
